                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 772.73/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to King
                            <persName type="to">Nicholas I</persName> of Montenegro</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-09">9 January,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Good Friend</hi>: I have received your letter of January
                    seventh and read it with considerable interest. I must at present content myself
                    with a brief acknowledgment of it, but I beg that you will believe that the days
                    will not be too crowded or too hurried for me to drive the interests of sturdy
                    Montenegro out of my mind or to lessen in the least my sincere desire to do
                    everything in my power to see that justice is done her. The matters to which you
                    call my attention will have my most serious and sympathetic consideration.</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
